The paper deals with computer vision problems, specifically sparse coding and dictionary learning, which are typically addressed in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Riemannian manifolds and kernel methods also suggests a possible fit with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The proposed algorithm for solving the Lasso problem efficiently may also be relevant to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the use of kernel methods and Hilbert spaces may also suggest a possible fit with the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
